    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for ruby4.0.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Ruby is the interpreted scripting language for quick and easy object-oriented programming.  It has many features to process text files and to do system management tasks (as in Perl).  It is simple, straight-forward, and extensible.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* ruby/json: Ruby JSON: Denial of Service or Information Disclosure via format string injection (CVE-2026-33210)\n\n* erb: ERB: Arbitrary code execution via deserialization bypass (CVE-2026-41316)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
